{"title": "The new Great Game has melting Arctic ice all over it", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-01-18", "content": "In late December, as the world prepared for the Christmas holiday season, the United States announced on the State Department website that it had extended its continental shelf in several key regions of the world, but principally the Arctic.\nIn all, the US mapping \u2013 conducted over 20 years \u2013 led it to claim rights to an additional 987,700 sq km, an area about twice the size of California."}